  "text": "E. LAMB Syndrome e Incorrect. LAMB syndrome, now referred to as Carney complex, is a multiple endocrine neoplasia syndrome characterized by lentigines, atrial myxomas, and blue nevi. Lentigines in LAMB syndrome typically manifest in the first 2 decades of life, and there is no mention of blue nevi or cardiac findings in this patient's history. A. Palms and soles e Incorrect. There have been few reported cases involving the palms and soles. Addison's disease is characterized by pronounced hyperpigmentation of the palms and soles in addition to the perineum, axillae, and areaolae. [CITATION_1] B. Nails e Correct. Melanonychia has been described in up to 60% of cases of LaugierHunziker syndrome. [CITATION_2] Nail involvement usually presents as single-or double-striped longitudinal lines. Fingernails are more commonly affected than toenails.",
